definition: "to eat" or "food" radical in Chinese characters (Kangxi radical 184)
to cover/to wrap/to hold/to include/to take charge of/to contract (to or for)/package/wrapper/container/bag/to hold or embrace/bundle/packet/CL:個|个[ge4],隻|只[zhi1]
to endure/to suffer/to be subjected to
to have enough food and warm clothes/adequately provided
to be full of (emotion)/to brim with (love, tears etc)
to look intensively/to feast one's eyes on
to enjoy fully/to experience to the full over a long period

pinyin: bu4 bao3 he2 zhi1 fang2 suan1

definition: to have eaten and drunk to one's heart's content
to stuff one's pockets/to take bribes
to eat and eat/to stuff oneself
to eat one's fill/to have a good meal

sentences.english: What if you mentally ate your fill?
sentences.chinese: 要是想像盡情喫個飽會怎樣？

sentences.english: Here are some things to consider so that your days are loaded with accomplishments.
sentences.chinese: 爲了你的每一天都飽有成就，你需要考慮的以下幾點。

sentences.english: We have given the hand to the Egyptians, and to the Assyrians, to be satisfied with bread.
sentences.chinese: 我們投降埃及人和亞述人，爲要得糧喫飽。

sentences.english: Because you tend to feel full sooner, you eat less of your main course.
sentences.chinese: 因爲喝湯會讓你很快覺得飽了，所以正餐就能少喫點。

sentences.english: Try to pay attention as you eat and stop when you're full.
sentences.chinese: 請儘量注意你的飽足感，如果你覺得飽了就不要再喫。

sentences.english: Before being fermented, the white chunks of tofu are plump and pliant . How filling they look!
sentences.chinese: 泡製前的豆腐塊白鼓鼓的，富彈性，很有飽實感。

sentences.english: Complete according to " had eaten in the morning, satiate midday, eat in the evening little " principle.
sentences.chinese: 完全按照“早上喫好，中午喫飽，晚上喫少”的原則。

sentences.english: I rely on my parents to feed and clothe me.
sentences.chinese: 我仰賴父母讓我喫飽穿暖。

sentences.english: Smaller bites also help your body realize when it’s full.
sentences.chinese: 小口喫飯也容易讓你的身體認識到自己喫飽了。

sentences.english: The mother cat could not feed them. One by one, all the kittens died.
sentences.chinese: 母貓喂不飽小貓，它們一個接一個都死了。

sentences.english: I stopped to feast my eyes on the cakes because I'm on diet.
sentences.chinese: 我正在減肥，所以只能到那些麪包房去飽飽眼福。

sentences.english: For I have inebriated the weary soul: and I have filled every hungry soul.
sentences.chinese: 因爲我要振作睏乏的心靈，飽飫一切苦悶的心靈。

sentences.english: Fluid column has been adopted in the research on adsorption of phenol in fine sandy soil saturated with water.
sentences.chinese: 採用流動柱法研究苯酚在飽水細砂土中的吸附。

sentences.english: I had never seen as much good food in my life, and I chowed down.
sentences.chinese: 我人生中從來沒見過這麼多好喫的東西，我吃了個飽。

sentences.english: As winter looms many North Koreans cannot feed or warm themselves.
sentences.chinese: 冬天已來臨，而朝鮮人們還喫不飽穿不暖。

sentences.english: At the end of the meal, everyone was very full.
sentences.chinese: 喫完飯以後，每個人都覺得非常飽。
